From f424a4db7ae23cdb14812cdc24ad3e875b8b5f49 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joakim Bech <Joakim.Bech@analog.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Feb 2026 12:48:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Fix compiler warnings and compilation errors across No-OS
 projects

This commit addresses a comprehensive set of compiler warnings and errors
throughout the No-OS codebase, improving code quality and ensuring clean
builds across all projects and drivers.

All (32) maxim platforms builds without errors using GCC 14.3 now.

Key fixes include:
- Remove 100+ unused variable warnings across drivers and projects
- Fix pointer-sign, enum-conversion, and discarded-qualifiers warnings
- Remove always-false NULL checks and type-limit comparisons
- Fix stringop-truncation and double-promotion warnings
- Add missing return statements and fix uninitialized variable warnings
- Replace deprecated API usage (MXC_RTC_GetSeconds)
- Convert #warning directives to comments to eliminate cpp warnings
- Fix unused function and label warnings in IIO and example code
- Resolve lwip compilation error in socket implementation

Affected components:
- Drivers: ADXL313, LTC2672, MAX538x, MAX14919, SSD1306, LTC4306,
  ADIN1110, LT7170, MAX17851, ADES1754
- Platform: Maxim DMA, RTC, and SPI implementations
- IIO subsystem: core, app, and daemon
- Network: lwip and TCP socket implementations
- Multiple project examples and common data files

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Joakim Bech <Joakim.Bech@analog.com>
